% HTML Document Ontology - CNL Format
% Natural English syntax for semantic HTML analysis
%
% This ontology provides concepts for HTML document analysis:
% - Document structure (documents, elements, forms)
% - Scripts and event handlers (with JavaScript integration)
% - Framework detection (Vue, Angular, HTMX, Alpine)
% - Links and resources (stylesheets, external scripts)

% ============================================================================
% Class Hierarchy (HTML-specific)
% ============================================================================

Every `html:DocumentEntity` is a `owl:Thing`.
Every `html:Document` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:Element` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:Script` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:ScriptReference` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:StyleSheet` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:Form` is a `html:Element`.
Every `html:FormInput` is a `html:Element`.
Every `html:Link` is a `html:Element`.
Every `html:Meta` is a `html:Element`.
Every `html:EventHandler` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:Image` is a `html:Element`.
Every `html:Iframe` is a `html:Element`.

% ============================================================================
% Framework Directives
% ============================================================================

Every `html:FrameworkIndicator` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
Every `html:VueDirective` is a `html:FrameworkIndicator`.
Every `html:AngularDirective` is a `html:FrameworkIndicator`.
Every `html:HtmxAttribute` is a `html:FrameworkIndicator`.
Every `html:AlpineDirective` is a `html:FrameworkIndicator`.
Every `html:DataAttribute` is a `html:DocumentEntity`.
